Concerned community members have collected and disposed of hundreds of the balls, placed deliberately in areas where dogs frequent.

Police still do not know who made the meatballs, believed to contain the poisonous substance strychnine, or left them in the street, but the investigation is ongoing.

They told residents at a community meeting last week that so far no reported pet deaths have been linked to the meatballs.

